Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: Nearly 57 retailers, including KIKO, Toys R Us, Hhgregg, Brookstone and Gymboree, have filed for bankruptcy protection so far in the last few years. What are the reasons behind that? Extremely high operating costs, adapting to e-commerce, insufficient supply chain management, inability to streamlining and optimizing product services.  At the same time such retail giants as Walmart, Hy-Vee, Carrefour go for blockchainization because they care about the origins of their products, the supply chain, communications between parties and consumerâ€™s needs and stay top retailers not minding the market changes. METRO C&C partners OSA DC to develop a solution that has proven to increase sales on average by 5,4%. It is clear that retail has the need for innovations and those who does not understand that, fall overboard.  "The third quarter confirms the positive trend in the vast majority of our business entities. It also shows that we can correct individual negative developments rapidly and effectively. We have continued the positive like-for-like sales trend in our wholesale segment, which accounts for 80% of our business activities in terms of sales. says Olaf Koch, Chairman of the Management Board of METRO AG  Metro C&C decided to improve product availability for its customers by deploying the OSA service through its supply chain. Author: TOM47
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: Big Brands Choose OSA DC and Blockchain to Drive Sales and Cut Product Waste https://medium.com/osadc/big-brands-choose-osa-dc-and-blockchain-to-drive-sales-and-cut-product-waste-bfb1a6a8ed3b    The worldâ€™s most prominent brands support OSA DC project and look for blockchain to bring sales increase and help cut product waste.  Recent research published by IDC Manufacturing Insights revealed that only 3.0% of the $35 billion in net growth in the consumer goods industry over the last three years has come from traditional, large enterprise players.  The majority of growth comes from young companies: the independents and start-ups. They have taken full advantage of an increasingly digital economy and evolving consumer demand for greater products variety, to win substantial market share from traditional players.  This forces traditional companies to better adapt to changing consumer behavior, as well as find new waysâ€Šâ€”â€Šthrough new products, sales channels, and distribution strategiesâ€Šâ€”â€Što remain relevant despite intense competition.  Recently a number of traditional companies have turned their attention to the promising blockchain technology, to help drive sales and establish product traceability. Among the most publicized was the IBM project with the worldâ€™s biggest retail chain, Walmart, called Food Traceability. Aiming to be able to trace in seconds the provenance of any product, this project has received a lot of attention.  Yet the insiders report that the results of the project is little more than ticking on the â€œcompletedâ€ box,â€Šâ€”â€Šas the real bottleneck appeared in the quality of the data that had to be recorded on the blockchain. As they sayâ€Šâ€”â€Šshit inâ€Šâ€”â€Šshit outâ€¦ And of course, putting it on blockchain does not make it any betterâ€¦  OSA DC, an ambitious blockchain start-up claims that it has the answer to this issue. They found the solution in combining big data, artificial intelligence with blockchain. OSA DC starts by gathering relevant big data from more than 100 open and private sources, cleans, processes and analyses it, and only then secures relevant hashes in the blockchain, to achieve information immutability and trustworthiness by all parties involved.  This approach allowed OSA DC to develop a solution that has proven to increase sales on average by 5,4%. Tested in a major retail chain and with support and supervision from major consumer goods manufacturers, the project immediately caught attention. Today OSA DC boasts the worldâ€™s leading manufacturers as their clients. The company provides services to major international brands including Coca-Cola, Mars, Lâ€™Oreal, Nestle, and Metro Cash & Carry.  Recently OSA DC announced news that Nestle, worldâ€™s biggest consumer goods company, joined the OSA project. Before Nestle participated to IBM blockchain project. With the help of OSA services, the company aims to improve its supply chain processes, reduce product waste and save billions of dollars annually. Nestle Customer Development and Supply Chain Manager, Ekaterina Lihacheva, points out that â€œshelf availability is a crucial problem which can be solved only with the help of innovative technologies, implemented by OSA.â€  Nestleâ€™s priority is to improve supply chain insufficiencies so the product can always be available for the consumer. The company believes that OSA is an excellent solution as it allows for optimal product logistics and delivery.  Combined turnover of OSA DC big brands clients is 305 billion dollars! This is roughly 1.5 times bigger than the current value of all cryptocurrencies combined!  We keep wonderingâ€Šâ€”â€Šas the whole crypto world is holding its breath for a new miracle, ever since January 2018â€Šâ€”â€Šcould start-ups like OSA DC really become the salvation for the crypto world, the next wave, by finally implementing blockchain technology in the real economy. Andâ€Šâ€”â€Šletâ€™s not forget that consumer goods retail is the worldâ€™s biggest industry.

Author: OSA_DC
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: Ethereum has failed us.  Alex Isaiev, the CEO of OSA, sadly admits: â€œI was motivated by Vitaliy Buterinâ€™s speech on blockchain urgently requiring real life applications. We relied upon Ethereum (Quorum-based on Ethereum) for our private chain solution, although we knew about system limitations at that time.  The system was not initially designed to address the enterprise solutionâ€™s needs. Ethereum presents only rigid data frames, unadjustable for business needs. The cost of the transaction is another unfriendly side of the Ethereum chain as it levels any business profit provided by other blockchain related benefits. The last, but probably the most pressing system weakness, is the process of tokens distribution with lock up strategies.  While they spend enormous efforts on PR and grand statements, other humble companies are working on actually developing unique and effective solutions. OSA has announced competition for long-standing technological partnerships. MOUs were signed with Intervalue, IPchain, HPB, Everitoken and Penta followed by a row of successful tests of these blockchain protocols. It seems Ethereum is not so indispensable and universal as itâ€™s trying to appear after all.  https://medium.com/osadc/etherium-fail-how-the-blockchain-giant-let-down-its-supporters-223a9198f53a

Author: OSA_DC
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: Coca-Cola Chooses Blockchain.   Earlier this year Coca Cola announced the blockchainisation of labor contracts.  This time blockchain will help 188 B company to improve supply chain and decrease losses that are estimated at an average of 11% across the beverages industry.  https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/03/coca-cola-verify-suppliers-blockchain-180317125204446.html   "Our mission is to become the leading supply chain function in our industry in terms of customer service and cost efficiency." - says Marcel Martin, Coca Cola HBC Supply Chain Director.  OSA DC, a retail solutions provider that uses AI and blockchain to optimize supply chain efficiency, currently runs a project with Coca Cola in 3 retail chains, ensuring product availability on the shelf level at all times for shoppers. The Blockchain mission is to establish an environment of trust and optimize business processes between manufacturers and retailers, in addition it delivering big savings for both parties.

OSA DC reduces the costs associated with the search for and removal of unsafe food and to significantly reduce the number of deaths and illnesses due to toxic products. https://medium.com/osadc/china-food-safety-is-a-major-issue-4cc7a8228b26

Author: OSA_DC
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: The application of blockchain technology is currently being tested in the logistics, healthcare, energy, and retail industries, all with their own unique purposes. Not surprisingly,  such biggest retail brands as Walmart, Metro and Hy-Vee choose blockchain for the entire supply chain transparency.  Blockchain technology implementation will dramatically  increase efficiency and save the health of the customers, helping to avoid overstock, low quality and hazardous goods being accepted by retail chains.  METRO Cash & Carry, an international self-service wholesaler giant, took a decision to enhance traceability capabilities and product data. A win-win solution for all , manufacturers, retailers and customers, OSA is currently testing blockchain and AI implementation in 2 branches. The results show the 70+ % alert accuracy of the absence of goods on the shelf in real time and opens new perspectives for the retailer.  Blockchain technology implementation will dramatically efficiency and save retailers around 500 billion loses annually.

Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: Vice President of Walmart and OSA DC Advisor Don Swann, interview https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aZ2cDrxsLsc&feature=youtu.be  Don is an accomplished retail operations and merchandising executive who thrives on the challenge of building successful retail operations by using proven and cutting-edge innovations in multi-cultural environments. He has indisputable expertise in retail strategy and tactical execution, and has built a skillset for maximizing profitability through building, coaching, and leading management teams to deliver business success. Don has spent more than 50 years in various roles with Wal-Mart, the world's largest retailer, developing operating systems, training, working in human resources, and managing store operations. After a successful career with Walmart serving as VP of operations and COO in the U.S., Canada, Russia, and Brazil, Don is now the CEO of Cygnus Familia, a global consulting business located in the United States.

Author: OSA_DC
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: OSA DC welcomes its partners and crypto community leaders from China and Japan to Moscow! The 4 day session started with a Dixy store visit - one of the largest retailers in Russia. Meetings with the OSA DC managing team took place at our Moscow office to discuss OSA technology implementation in retail, business development and OSA expansion in the Asian market. Meeting with GigaWatt - a large mining farm and OSA's partner, a business breakfast with "Dixy" and "Vernyi" representatives - one of the leading retailer trade networks, along with meeting Alex Ohlopkov, Mars Supply Chain Director, capped with an exciting tour through the historic and beautiful Moscow city!

Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: OSA Global Roadshow Beijing Station is Successfully Finished!  July 28 afternoon, OSA Company in Tianchuang Technology Building 406 successfully held the Beijing Station Road Show! OSA's Beijing road show was attended by nearly two dozen well-known enterprises, such as Congregating Capital, Gravity Capital, Chain Capital, Enabling Capital, Bull Market Finance and Economics.  Road show place Tianchuang Science and Technology Building 406 in China blockchain history has an extraordinary significance, here witnessed all the glories of the circle of currency chain! Because of the air-conditioning failure that day, in the sweltering summer of the office, all the guests in this brilliant office witnessed the OSA's enthusiasm!  The OSA project was highly appreciated by all the guests. The founder, Mr. Alex, Mr. Anton, Mr. Max and the guests had an in-depth exchange on the project itself and the blockchain industry, although the room temperature reached 32 degrees, However, the enthusiasm of all, after the road show, the restaurant moved to a more in-depth exchange, in the following week, the OSA project side will have more in-depth contacts with the enterprises on investment and cooperation.     https://i.imgur.com/9LrLafy.jpg https://i.imgur.com/o1CMwJb.jpg

Author: Trancelator
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: â–²â–²â–²          OSA DC's solution to major retail problems  OSADC  Every year, the consumer product retail industry loses over $400bln in revenue due to in-store product availability issues. This is a result of lack transparency and and widespread inefficiencies in the entire supply chain. In addition, the retail industry wastes over $100bln in products annually. OSA DC is the worldâ€™s first solution for real-time retail supply chain improvements. Our big data platform analyses more than 100 data points and factors that influence consumer behavior. OSA DC is artificial intelligence engine also examines in-store data to recognize if something goes wrong with a product on its shelf or in its aisle. The AI engine then sends alerts to the storeâ€™s staff to manage and correct the situation. Our image recognition engine will direct employees towards stock-outs, assist in executing a task to solve the problem, and collect additional data. By doing so, OSA DC can deliver sales growth of over 5% to retailers and manufacturers and optimizes their costs (OSA HP, OSA DCâ€™s predecessor, has already accomplished this feat). To secure data from manipulation and automate business processes, OSA DC deploys blockchain and smart contract functionality. As such, OSA provides reliable data, establishes an environment of trust, and increases profit. OSA DC significantly reduces product waste. For Smart Consumers Only! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QBvj5LZUwaI&feature=youtu.be  OSA DC is the world's first decentralized, AI-driven marketplace, providing real-time solutions to retailers, manufacturers, and consumers.  The Retail industry loses approximately $500 billion annually. OSA DC reduces this waste by uniting producers, retailers, and consumers with its blockchain-empowered solutions.  The OSA platform provides consumers with transparent product information and online assistant services, while OSA DCâ€™s AI-powered ecosystem gives manufacturers and retailers the chance to collaborate effectively and optimize their business strategies.  OSA DC unites consumers into a single powerful community, giving them the power over the manufacturers and retailers of consumer goods, so that consumers can determine what products they really want, when, where, and at what prices.

Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: OSA DC in collaboration with Cryptocurrency Lab, Korea University, is proud to announce the first AI Seminar in Seoul, Korea!  The Blockchain & AI Workshop will take place on July 19th, at Crimson Hall, 12FL, Media Hall, Korea University, and will gather our partners, OSA DC contributors, and AI specialists from Korean Technical University.  Opening speeches will be given by Professor Sang Jin Lee, the President of School of Information Security. AI, Blockchain, and Big Data presentations will be given by leading representatives of The Gwangju Institute of Science and Technology, College of Engineering, Seoul National University, and the OSA DC team. A whole lot more is waiting for you to learn about the implementation of innovate technologies in Retail!  Stay tuned to follow our news and live broadcast from the AI Seminar, Korea!

Body: Maximilian Musselius serves as the Strategy and Vision Lead for OSA DC. He is also an Executive Director of ECR (Efficient Consumer Response) Russia and Co-chairman of ECR Europe. Max is the author of numerous research and analytical articles in the ï¬eld of fast-moving consumer goods (FMCG) manufacturing and retail, including ECR Bluebook, EDI Bluebook, Scorecard Bluebook by ECR Russia, Global ECR and ECR-Rus Master Data Bluebook, and Global Scorecard.  Prior to ECR, Max held various marketing positions in International consultancies. He is a Moscow State University graduate with degrees in law and economics and speaks six languages.  Dylan Robertson, who is a Chief Growth Officer CoinJinja had a chance to chat with Maximilian Japan Blockchain Conference in Tokyo to learn more about the story behind OSA DC and where the project is heading. https://medium.com/coinview/maximilian-musselius-strategy-vision-lead-osa-dc-interview-877ef05b5901

Author: MihailJ
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: Smart Shopping: OSA DC Makes Consumers Change the Future of Traditional Retail In retail, unlike in wholesale, consumersâ€™ opinions and interactions play vital roles in the rise and fall of the market. It is the consumersâ€™ opinions, turning into demands, that affect the overall understocking or overstocking of shelves. This opinion now costs about $400 billion in sales losses annually. With an ever growing number of retailers offering all imaginable goods, buyers are becoming pickier and sometimes weary of the constant need to make choices. But,what if options get easier? What if personal preferences, age, financial ability or diet restrictions are taken into account by the retailer who sifts out the chaff and offers only the best, most suitable options? What if before you actually buy something, you get usersâ€™ feedback about the item without staging a time consuming Google investigation? And what if you have the opportunity to get a reward for information inputs on your products of interest? That certainly makes it worth a personal contribution to the market. https://medium.com/osadc/smart-shopping-osa-dc-makes-consumers-change-the-future-of-traditional-retail-cb2b3cc70da7

Author: alexvilis
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: Interview with Mikhail Myagkov, PhD, OSA DC Game Theory and Data Science Advisory Board Lead https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MKmBusVLrjE  Professor Myagkov has over 20 years of teaching experience in the United States. He's a tenured professor at the of University of Oregon's Institute of Cognitive and Decision Sciences and Politology Department. He is also a professor at Moscow State University and Skolkovo Institute of Science and Technology (Skoltech), where he founded a number of its first innovation and academic programs. Mikhail holds PhD, MS and BS degrees from the California Institute of Technology (Caltech) with a focus in managements, applied mathematics, and game theory. Mikhailâ€™s academic interests lie in game theory, behavioral economics, agent-based computer simulations of human decision making, applied statistics, neuroeconomics, and decision making analysis based on computer imaging technologies.

Author: Silicat1510
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: About OSA OSA Decentralized (OSA DC) is the world's first decentralized AI-driven marketplace providing real-time solutions to retailers, manufacturers and consumers.  OSA is a successful existing business established in 2015. We provide services for world leading consumer product retail and manufacturers, including Coca-Cola, PepsiCo, JTI, Mars, L'Oreal, Metro Cash & Carry, and many others.  After two years of development in close partnership with ECR organization that unites more than 70 leading manufacturers and retailers, we developed proof of concept in 2016, and as of 2017 deployed OSA Hybrid Platform (OSA HP) - Big Data platform powered by AI that manages products optimal shelf availability in retail stores in real time.  Optimal shelf availability is the biggest problem in global consumer retail, costing manufacturers and retailers 400 billion dollars in lost sales per year. It is caused by business processes' inefficiencies along the supply chain and in the retail stores. OSA HP integrates with the big data systems of the participating retail chains and then combines optical recognition and machine learning technologies to issue alerts to the in-store staff each time our algorithms discover there might be a problem with optimal shelf availability of the products being distributed by our clients.

Author: S3cco
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: Bitcoin Garden: Reshaping Shopping with Blockchain and AI â€“ OSA DC Launches Token Sale https://bitcoingarden.org/reshaping-shopping-with-blockchain-and-ai-osa-dc-launches-token-sale/  OSA Decentralized (OSA DC), a team of experts in artificial intelligence, blockchain technology and the retail industry, has launched a token sale. The companyâ€™s goal is to use capital raised in the sale to scale their AI-powered blockchain platform and provide the entire retail industry with a much-needed digital overhaul.  Due to antiquated, analog-based systems still used in product ordering, shipping, and inventory management, retailers lose more than $400 billion each year. This also causes overstocking or under stocking, as many stores fail in their efforts to manage inventory based on customer demand. Supermarkets and grocery store chains lose an additional $100 billion annually when high volumes of unsold perishable foods pass their expiration dates and are discarded.  OSA DCâ€™s data and retail experts are dedicated to bringing order to the industryâ€™s chaos by leveraging their AI, blockchain and smart contract technology. This will ensure that every bit of data generated by manufacturers, farmers, shipping companies, or grocery stores on a retailerâ€™s supply chain is tracked by everyone else. Because of the transparent and incorruptible technical characteristics of a distributed ledger system that defines blockchain technology, OSA is confident there will be greater trust between retailers and their partners and product waste will be eliminated....

Body: Bitcoin Garden: TaaS partners with OSA DC To Build Global Smart Consumer Platform https://bitcoingarden.org/taas-partners-with-osa-dc-to-build-global-smart-consumer-platform/  Token-as-a-Service (TaaS), the worldâ€™s first tokenized closed-end fund dedicated to blockchain assets, has entered into a partnership with OSA DC, a tokenized AI and blockchain solution for the retail and supply chain industries with an ambition to build the largest global  consumer retail community.  As a closed-end fund, TaaS is dedicated to the development and enrichment of the cryptocurrency ecosystem. The service features a smart-contract profit sharing model that awards TAAS token holders with shares of its capital fund gains, a cryptocurrency fund managed by a team of TaaS traders and investors. In addition to this capital fund profit sharing, the service contributes to and invests in promising blockchain projects, and it also serves as an advisory arm for rising stars in the industry to help them accomplish their long-term business development goals.  TaaS first took interest in OSA DC through the D10E conference series. The series brings together hundreds of decentralized and FinTech projects in venues all over the world, and TaaS has cooperated with D10E to invest in the promising start-ups it brings to its events. After OSA DC won 1st place at the D10E conference in South Korea for best start-up, TaaS approached the project for a partnership. TaaS finds value in OSA DCâ€™s AI-driven marketplace and smart contract solutions, and given the proven success of OSA DCâ€™s mother company, the OSA Hybrid Platform, which has delivered results to over 20 retailers and manufacturers around Europe, TaaS has faith in the future success of the product....

Author: HappyMod
Title: [ANN][ICO] OSA DC - AI and Blockchain meet Retail
Body: Great questions and activity everyone! If there are more questions let us know, we will be answering all questions, every day! Sorry for waiting.     Hi Bixbem90! I would love to help you regarding exchanges. However, at this point there is no available information regarding this. Co-Founder Alex did share a post on the second of April on Telegram: ''Met the CoinNest, the 5th largest exchange in Korea. Guys are creating the incubator. We found Lots of opportunities for collaboration. To be continued...'.  Quote from: coinswebid on April 13, 2018, 02:37:06 AM i read about this, and i want a little explanations   Soft Cap ETH/USD: Already achieved how much funds as the soft cap collected ? and where this funds coming from ? is this funds come from the founders,? Quote  The founders have already contributed $4.2MLN USD towards the development and deployment of the platform.  Hi coinswebid, Right! The founders have already contributed 4.2MLN USD towards the development and deployment of the platform, giving OSA DC a great start! I will look with the team to confirm this for you You can already join the whitelist for the public pre sale right now, at http://osadc.io  Quote from: fromkrec on April 13, 2018, 08:40:05 AM Quote from: dolcevita99 on April 13, 2018, 07:47:52 AM The project has just started its work, but I see support already. The idea of the project is magnificent and very interesting! The combination of the two technologies and at the same time it will be useful for us. Popularity in the scope of the Blockchain is growing, so we will see in the near future a good growth of the Crypto-currency. in fact, the exchange rate has already started to rise slowly. And in connection with these, I had a question, is not this a large amount for investing - 1 eth per token?  Thank you for the support, and the minimum amount to participate was set by the team. We have no influence on this, but as you can see, the hardcap is $80,000,000, in which 1 ETH is not a lot. 1 ETH min. should make participation available for a lot of interested members  Quote from: Hodlvcl on April 13, 2018, 08:48:16 AM I understand that this is a project to collect data from retailers, manufacturers, consumers, and then what do you do with the amount of data collected?   Great questions. There is a lot that can be done with the collected data, and you can learn a lot more in the whitepaper (https://osadc.io/assets/files/white-paper/white-paper-osadc-en.pdf). For example, it can be used for forecasting. ''Typically, enterprise forecasting systems are focused on distribution centers to warehouses to retail store chain. The purpose of the forecast is to avoid overstocking and ensure appropriate restocking, the forecasting period can vary from one day to several weeks.  OSA is not limited to providing stock replenishment forecasts. Our in-store help customers to better understand their current situation, whether in real-time or within the fastest data collection interval a clientâ€™s IT infrastructure can provide. OSAâ€™s instore analysis helps to proactively solve any issues and detect their root causes (e.g., price tag missing, product packaging damaged, expiration date issue). We also provide product to make sure that alerts not only arrive to clients, but that the problems receive due and timely attention from the storeâ€™s employees.'' Page 14-19 in the whitepaper will give you plenty of examples!  Quote from: JuggSlash on April 14, 2018, 06:43:47 AM Quote from: LancienMaleAlpha on April 13, 2018, 09:25:02 PM quite an interesting project, which can raise effectiveness of retailing business. Like the idea itself, as it spreads retailing horizons. But wanted to ask some questions - how many companies you want to involve in that and have you already had some kind of partnerships with some retailers? I hope so. But, don't expect they had some kind of partnerships with a big industry like Google or Amazon, this is just a small company perhaps.   You can read a lot about the partnerships in our whitepaper (https://osadc.io/assets/files/white-paper/white-paper-osadc-en.pdf) Here is some examples from the road map: 2015: Partnerships with L'Oreal, Efes, JTI to implement OSA Hybrid Platform 2016: Partnership with Coca-Cola, Danone to implement OSA Hybrid Platform 2017:Partnerships with Mars and SunInBev to implement OSA Hybrid Platform, Partnership with Neuromation, Partnership with DLA Piper for business support in the USA, OSA Hybrid Platform partners and integrates with 10 retail chains and 12 manufacturers  Quote from: Arvilaine on April 14, 2018, 01:55:18 PM There has been a lot of AI built to help Retailers and Consumers to make it easier for them to get the good that they need, can you create a comparison chart that will be able to differentiate this project from those projects or maybe make it more competitive?
